The "bird flu" outbreak in Hong Kong has claimed four lives, including a 54-year-old man.
Health officials are monitoring staff with flu-like symptoms.
Imported poultry is deemed safe, with no evidence of human-to-human transmission.
Macao residents are advised to buy poultry from licensed vendors.
Experts are puzzled by the virus, but no epidemic has been declared.
Precautions include avoiding contact with birds and maintaining good immunity.
Despite cases in Hong Kong, there have been no reports of bird flu in Macao.
